          <p class="font_18 about_desc">
            Ms. Hoster serves as a Managing Partner with Family Office Architects, where she
leads operations, due diligence, reporting and client services. Ms. Hoster has over 20+
years of experience in working with family offices and institutional partners within real
estate, alternative energy and asset management services. Most recently Ms. Hoster
served as the Vice President of Investment Operations of MAP, an acquirer and
manager of natural gas, wind energy, and utility-scale solar energy royalty interests
within the United States. Prior roles included a focus on asset management,
acquisitions/dispositions and operations as Assistant Vice President for Somera Capital
Management (The Firestone Family Office), Assistant Vice President of Centurion Real
Estate Partners (multi-family office), Director of Investor Relations at Keystone Property
Trust, an industrial REIT and Analyst/Associate with PaineWebber Real Estate Principal
Group (now UBS). Ms. Hoster has extensive oversite experience with the various real
estate product types of multi-family, hotels, industrial, office and multi-use in value-
added renovation, acquisition/disposition and new development throughout the United
States.
            <br>
            <br>
            Ms. Hoster served as Board Member and Treasurer of Stanford Professional Women
and currently leads the Colorado Chapter, and has served on the Junior League as
Chair and Co- Chair positions in the Denver, New York, San Francisco, Palo Alto and
Los Angeles Chapters. She continues to volunteer for Stanford University in fundraising and
interviewing potential Stanford undergraduate candidates. Ms. Hoster is a graduate of
Stanford University, Palo Alto, CA.
            <br>
            <br>
            <span class="font_italic">Ms. Hoster is a Registered Representative and licensed to sell securities through March
Capital Corporation, a Member of FINRA and SIPC.</span>
